Arsenal had a €35 million bid rejected for the France international last week with Lyon wanting around €60m for the midfielder. Arsenal have been unable to negotiate a deal to sign Aouar after continued discussions with the Ligue 1 club. Aouar was the club’s priority this summer ahead of Atletico Madrid’s Thomas Partey, who has a release clause of €50m. Arsenal boss Mikel Arteta is desperate to secure a loan deal for Jorginho before the transfer window closes on Monday. Jorginho scored two penalties as Chelsea cruised to a comfortable 4-0 victory over Crystal Palace on Saturday. Chelsea would be reluctant to allow Jorginho to depart without signing another defensive midfielder but Frank Lampard recognises the need to reduce a bloated squad before Monday’s deadline.